# LabelForge — environment reference
#
# No .env file is required for local development.
# All credentials are hardcoded in backend/dependencies.py.
#
# ── Quick-start ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   make setup   # one-time install
#   make dev     # starts both servers
#
# ── URLs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   Frontend  →  http://localhost:5173
#   API docs  →  http://localhost:8000/docs
#   Health    →  http://localhost:8000/api/health
#
# ── Credentials ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   admin / admin123  →  /admin  (full editor: bbox, font, color)
#   user  / user123   →  /user   (text replacement only)
#
# ── Common make targets ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   make setup      one-time bootstrap
#   make dev        start backend + frontend
#   make test       run pytest
#   make lint       ruff + mypy
#   make clean      wipe venv, node_modules, DB
#   make help       list all targets
